1
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:36,440
<i>I've waited</i>
<i>Waited so long</i>

2
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:39,080
The apple doesn't fall far from the tree.

3
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,680
‪PREVIOUS EPISODE

4
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,560
They're searching everywhere
for the hidden stash.

5
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,760
This looks like drugs.

6
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,120
- Come here.
- Come here.

7
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,160
- What?
- Bomb!

8
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,880
Are you alright?

9
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,800
I don't want to go to the hospital.

10
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:04,640
Right now, I live with Uncle Tharin,
my father's younger brother.

11
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,160
Do you know my father too?

12
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,960
And who are you?

13
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:22,920
Teacher Mueangphrai and Aunt Wilai
brought some fruit for you.

14
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,800
I'll go put it inside.

15
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,280
Once you're done,

16
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,120
could you go buy some Oliang

17
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:33,600
for your uncle and me?

18
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:37,520
But if I go buy it at the market,

19
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,640
it might take a while.

20
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:41,120
That's alright. I can wait.

21
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,880
I'll be right back.

22
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,960
Okay.

23
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:53,720
Please, have a seat first.
Thank you so much

24
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,000
for helping my niece last night.

25
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,760
You haven't changed at all, Phupha.

26
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:20,760
I'm sorry.

27
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,200
I'm Tharin.

28
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:27,080
I'm not Phupha.
I'm his twin younger brother.

29
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,760
Your mouth may say you're Tharin.

30
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:37,200
But your eyes say otherwise.

31
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:41,360
I don't know what you want,

32
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:44,240
suddenly forcing me to be Phupha,

33
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:46,640
when my brother died 20 years ago.

34
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:49,200
I want the truth.

35
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,840
For 20 years,

36
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,480
I've been searching
for witnesses and evidence

37
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,560
to expose what really happened.

38
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,640
I don't want Phupha,

39
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:04,560
Onanong, and Namthip

40
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,600
to have died
because they were falsely accused

41
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,440
of being lovers who killed each other

42
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,080
out of jealousy.

43
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,440
Calm down. Don't cry.

44
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,680
For 20 years,

45
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,040
I've cried every single day.

46
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:27,800
Meanwhile, those people

47
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,440
have walked free and lived in comfort.

48
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,600
Only you and I

49
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:37,600
are still drowning in this pain.

50
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,600
Phupha,

51
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,840
stop hiding.

52
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:47,560
Let's expose the truth.

53
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,360
Even if we die,

54
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:52,160
let us die with the truth.

55
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,680
Not with this shame hanging over us.

56
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,440
I'm Tharin.

57
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,160
I'm not Phupha.

58
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:10,040
If you keep expecting me to be him,

59
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,840
we'll never be able to talk.

60
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,880
Please leave.

61
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:18,360
Phupha. Phupha!

62
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,840
You can't do this.

63
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,600
We've suffered enough.

64
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,320
It's time for us to strike back.

65
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,680
If not for yourself,

66
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,440
then at least think of Poona.

67
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:36,440
Do you really want her
to live in shame for the rest of her life

68
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,640
because of the scandal
involving her parents?!

69
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:57,160
Anyone who wants to know
about Poona, come right here.

70
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,680
I can tell you everything.

71
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,400
Listen, everyone.

72
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:03,440
Poona's father was a singer named Phupha.

73
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:06,640
Her mother was Namthip.

74
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:08,000
Then Phupha ended up

75
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:10,600
having an affair
with another singer named Onanong.

76
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,840
In the end, they killed each other.

77
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,440
So shameless.

78
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:19,560
- That's disgusting.
- I know, right?

79
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,200
It's really awful.

80
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:36,560
Think carefully about this.
The child did nothing wrong,

81
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:39,520
yet she has to face
the insults and humiliation

82
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,920
caused by the lies told about her parents.

83
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,360
Everyone

84
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,600
will keep condemning Poona
for the rest of her life

85
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,080
because of your cowardice.

86
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:56,960
That's enough, Wilai.
Nothing good will come of this.

87
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,160
Stop talking right now.

88
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,120
I'm not a coward.

89
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,240
The reason I won't let Poona
become a singer

90
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:09,640
is because I care about her.

91
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,760
You've seen their cruelty yourself,
haven't you?

92
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,120
Are you worried about her,

93
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,360
or are you afraid they'll find you?

94
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,480
I've never been afraid.

95
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:24,320
Whatever happens, happens.

96
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:28,720
But she still has a bright future
ahead of her.

97
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,000
I don't want my niece

98
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:33,200
getting dragged into that vicious cycle.

99
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:34,159
Phupha.

100
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:37,480
Tharin. I'm Tharin.

101
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,280
That's enough, Wilai.

102
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,120
He told you his name is Tharin.

103
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,919
You're still forcing him to be Phupha.

104
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:44,840
That's not right.

105
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:48,760
You can fool anyone you want.

106
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,560
But…

107
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,280
I'll always recognize you.

108
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,480
I know

109
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:04,480
how you felt about my brother.

110
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:10,600
But I'm Tharin, not Phupha.

111
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,480
Fine.

112
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,360
If you won't admit it,

113
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,480
then so be it.

114
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:32,240
I can't force you to be Phupha.

115
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,720
But there's something I want you to know.

116
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:39,680
On that day,

117
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:44,200
in the final moment
before the car exploded,

118
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,480
I survived.

119
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:51,240
But I paid for it
with this ruined body and face.

120
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:54,040
From the beautiful Onanong,

121
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,920
I became Wilai, a disfigured woman.

122
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,040
I've been forced

123
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,800
to live in hiding.

124
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,080
All these years,

125
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,280
I've suffered.

126
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:16,400
I've been in so much pain.

127
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:52,440
<i>If you happen to read this letter</i>

128
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:55,360
<i>Destroy it when you're done</i>

129
00:10:55,440 --> 00:11:00,600
<i>Burn it if you wish</i>

130
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:03,320
<i>Don't keep it</i>

131
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:07,000
<i>In case your lover finds it</i>

132
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,920
<i>Don't let him see the photograph</i>

133
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:15,160
<i>Or he'll become suspicious</i>

134
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:20,000
On, do you think so?

135
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:24,080
Phupha's voice is truly captivating.

136
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:28,440
But there's a sadness hidden in it.

137
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,280
That's the kind of thing listeners love.

138
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:35,320
Yes, Phupha is a singer

139
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:39,000
who sings straight from his heart
and his own feelings.

140
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:42,400
That's why every song he performs

141
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:44,440
comes out so beautifully.

142
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,840
You're the same, On.

143
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,480
The songs you sing

144
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,960
are just as moving.

145
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,600
It's like music
descending from heaven itself.

146
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:00,280
On.

147
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:03,040
Do you know how proud I am of you?

148
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,200
I'm so proud of you.

149
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,000
Thank you.

150
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,040
Come on.

151
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:11,600
Let's go listen to Phupha
recording his new song.

152
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:14,160
- Come on.
- Sorry.

153
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,080
Excuse me for a moment.
I'll catch up in a moment.

154
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,800
- I'll go ahead then.
- Okay.

155
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,480
- I'll wait for you.
- Okay.

156
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,360
Auntie, how's the cake?

157
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:38,400
Here it is. It says,
"Happy Birthday, Kamnan Pong," too.

158
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,320
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, KAMNAN PONG

159
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:41,840
Great. Just leave it right here for now.

160
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,600
Keep the box closed. Don't open it yet.

161
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,880
I'll bring him in,

162
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,960
pretending it's about work,
then let him open it himself.

163
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,120
I want to surprise him.

164
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,880
Yes, Ms. On.

165
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:54,920
Did you bring the camera
for the secret video?

166
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,520
Yes, I did. It's in the bag.

167
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:01,160
Okay, thank you.

168
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,400
I'll handle the rest.

169
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,800
- Yes, Ms. On.
- Alright.

170
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,640
<i>I have no blessing left to give</i>

171
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:33,480
<i>Not even a single plea, my dear</i>

172
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:36,040
<i>Don't worry about a poor man</i>

173
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:39,560
<i>Who lives on simple meals</i>

174
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:43,200
<i>Go on, go enjoy the finer things</i>

175
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:48,560
<i>Rest your head on crisp banknotes</i>
<i>If that makes you happy</i>

176
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:51,280
<i>The photos</i>

177
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:55,360
<i>And letters of yours that I have</i>

178
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:58,000
<i>I'm returning them to you, my love</i>

179
00:13:58,080 --> 00:14:03,160
<i>I promise nothing has been damaged</i>

180
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,880
<i>The writing on the back has faded</i>

181
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:09,840
<i>As if even the signature has fallen away</i>

182
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:13,240
<i>I kiss it as tears run down my face</i>

183
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:19,720
<i>Please forgive me, my love</i>

184
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:25,320
<i>This is the very last letter</i>

185
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:28,120
<i>I won't trouble you anymore</i>

186
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:32,560
<i>Live freely, my darling</i>

187
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:36,040
<i>I have nothing to give you</i>

188
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:39,600
<i>On your wedding day</i>

189
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:43,480
<i>I only wish you good fortune</i>

190
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:46,680
I'm telling you,
once Phupha's song is released,

191
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:48,280
it's going to be a huge hit.

192
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:52,200
When am I going to get
a good song like this?

193
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,200
Wait for your turn, Singha.

194
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:57,960
I'm already looking for
a talented songwriter for you. I promise

195
00:14:58,640 --> 00:14:59,760
it'll be just as good as his.

196
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:04,040
<i>This is the very last letter</i>

197
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:07,440
<i>I won't trouble you anymore</i>

198
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:12,400
<i>Live freely, my darling</i>

199
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:14,760
<i>I have nothing to give you</i>

200
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:19,160
<i>On your wedding day</i>

201
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:22,560
<i>I only wish you good fortune</i>

202
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:26,400
<i>Let me say goodbye</i>

203
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:33,200
<i>Through this song</i>

204
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,800
Excellent.

205
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:50,120
You sang that really well.
Absolutely fantastic!

206
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,960
- Let's use this take, Phupha.
- Yes, sir.

207
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,560
What do you think, Singha?

208
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:56,400
Whatever you say, Kamnan.

209
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:57,560
I'm not good at judging these things.

210
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:01,840
If this song gets promoted properly,

211
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:04,720
trust me, it's definitely
going to be a hit.

212
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,640
Trust my ears, Phupha.

213
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,960
Thank you, Kamnan.

214
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,440
But if anyone's going to be famous,
it should be me.

215
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,960
I won the competition,

216
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,480
while Phupha only came in first runner-up.

217
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,880
How could he possibly become
more famous than me?

218
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:22,120
It all depends on fate.

219
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,800
You can't measure these things by rules.

220
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:25,960
Everyone has their own destiny.

221
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:32,760
If that's all, I'll get going.
I have something to do.

222
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:36,680
Is that so? Alright then,
once the mixing is finished,

223
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:39,560
I'll call you back
to listen to it. Alright?

224
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,560
- Thank you very much, Kamnan.
- Get some rest.

225
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,640
I'm off, Singha.

226
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,320
PUMPUANG DUANGJAN

227
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,880
What is it, Kitti? What happened?

228
00:17:06,119 --> 00:17:08,560
Just now, Chart called

229
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:11,319
and said the shipment we sent this time
got seized by the police.

230
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:14,000
How did it get busted?
Didn't you already pay them off?

231
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,920
The cops who made the arrest
came from central headquarters,

232
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,480
not the local station.

233
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,400
Oh no.

234
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:24,119
If they trace it back to us,

235
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,200
we're screwed.

236
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:27,839
Damn it.

237
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,120
I'll have Kamnan smooth things over.

238
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:36,440
Is anyone there?

239
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:09,920
Phupha?

240
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:19,320
About what we were talking about just now,

241
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:22,720
I'm sure Phupha heard us.

242
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,560
He must know we're dealing drugs.

243
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,880
Hey, we can't let him live, Kitti.

244
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:33,160
Relax. I'll take care of it myself.

245
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,440
How are you going to handle it?

246
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:36,640
With this gun.

247
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:40,680
If that's the case,
don't let it lead back to us.

248
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:43,640
How about this?

249
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:47,560
Have Chart go to his house

250
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:50,520
and make it look like an accident.
Sound good?

251
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:54,000
Yeah, good. As for you, go see Kamnan.

252
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,720
Make sure he smooths things over
about the drugs.

253
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,480
Phupha.

254
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:02,240
Phupha.

255
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,920
You're dead.

256
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:09,200
Oh, what's going on?
What are you doing in here?

257
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:19,600
Phupha. This is bad.

258
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,120
Singha.

259
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,160
SINGHA DARATHONG, THE GIFTED SINGER

260
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,040
I don't trust Onanong at all.

261
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:28,960
Don't worry.

262
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:32,840
Tonight, I'll destroy
both On and Phupha myself.

263
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:45,680
One of the crew secretly took these
during the MV shoot.

264
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:51,040
I never thought the two of them
would dare do something like this.

265
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,680
This isn't the first time.

266
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:59,240
The crew has seen them
together many times.

267
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,480
Thank you for telling me.

268
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:16,160
ONANONG WONGWICHIAN

269
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:19,760
Kamnan, there's one more thing.

270
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,880
Go on.

271
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:25,680
The van taking promo records
to the radio stations

272
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:28,480
got stopped by the police.

273
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:29,520
What's going on?

274
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,520
How dare the police
do something like this?

275
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:33,840
They're officers from headquarters.

276
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:38,720
I'll take care of it.

277
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:46,200
Hello, sir.

278
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,480
I need your help.

279
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:50,480
My business has run into a problem.

280
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,680
I'd like you to smooth things over for me.

281
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:57,640
Yes, sir. Thank you very much.

282
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,760
Send someone to get the goods back.

283
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:04,480
I've taken care of it.

284
00:21:04,560 --> 00:21:07,080
I see. And…

285
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:10,080
what should we do with Phupha?

286
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:14,200
Drag him here. If he won't come,

287
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,040
I'll deal with him myself.

288
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:25,200
What are you going to do?

289
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:28,800
Are you going to kill Phupha?

290
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,480
Onanong, why?

291
00:21:34,720 --> 00:21:36,160
Are you that worried about him?

292
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,800
I never imagined
that the person I loved most

293
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,200
would dare betray me.

294
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,760
I never imagined it either,

295
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:47,160
that the owner of a music label like you

296
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:50,440
would have such a filthy and cruel side.

297
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,520
Cruel enough to even kill
the singer you made into a star.

298
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:55,080
I can kill anyone.

299
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:58,640
I can even kill you, Onanong!

300
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:06,160
Come back! Get back here right now!

301
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,280
Kamnan!

302
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,840
I'll go after Ms. Onanong.

303
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:11,200
Please wait. Ms. Onanong!

304
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:12,840
Ms. Onanong!

305
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,320
Auntie, where's Poona?

306
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:20,600
She's asleep over there.

307
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,000
Oh? Alright.

308
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:26,240
Who's that coming?

309
00:22:35,040 --> 00:22:37,720
Tharin, Phupha's younger brother.

310
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,080
They look exactly alike.
I can't tell them apart.

311
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,680
You have to watch the way they walk.

312
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:44,600
Phupha and Tharin don't walk the same.

313
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,480
Namthip, is Phupha here?

314
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:51,600
No, he's not. He went to the music label.

315
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:55,680
Phupha asked me
to come get some of his old clothes.

316
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:58,600
He already set them aside.
They're at the house.

317
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,520
- We can go together.
- Okay.

318
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:05,680
Auntie, could you look after Poona for me?

319
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:06,680
Of course.

320
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:07,880
Thank you.

321
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:09,440
Let's go.

322
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,480
Phupha.

323
00:23:14,560 --> 00:23:16,680
Pick up, Phupha!

324
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:23,840
Pick up, Phupha!

325
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:26,160
Why aren't you answering?

326
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:33,640
Phupha, answer the phone. Phupha!

327
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,160
Chart.

328
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:45,200
Hello, Mr. Singha.

329
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:47,800
Once you've killed Phupha,

330
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:50,440
when Onanong gets there,

331
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:52,640
kill her too.

332
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:56,080
Then make it look like a love triangle,

333
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:58,440
<i>as if they were drinking,</i>
<i>got into a fight,</i>

334
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:02,040
and drove off the cliff.
Everyone in the car dies.

335
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:06,800
Yes, Mr. Singha. I'll take care of it.

336
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:23,800
I have to apologize
on behalf of my brother.

337
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,680
The ones at fault…

338
00:24:29,320 --> 00:24:30,840
are all of those people.

339
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,200
They made me like this.

340
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,160
Look at me.

341
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,800
Ever since the car explosion,

342
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:51,560
I've had to suffer
with this disfigured face.

343
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:57,000
I've had to endure being falsely accused

344
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:58,920
and having my reputation
completely destroyed.

345
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,840
As for your family,

346
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,760
you lost Namthip

347
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:09,320
and your own twin brother.

348
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:14,520
And you've had to live in hiding,

349
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:18,040
forced to endure the villagers' gossip.

350
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,160
Let me ask you this.

351
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:25,960
Are we supposed to endure this
for the rest of our lives?

352
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,120
I want revenge too.

353
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:32,200
But every time I look at Poona's face,

354
00:25:33,120 --> 00:25:34,400
I have to let it go.

355
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:38,120
Because I'm afraid.

356
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,920
I don't want Poona to be put in danger.

357
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:44,800
I can't bear any more loss.

358
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,400
But if we don't fight back,

359
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,840
we'll spend our whole lives
running from them.

360
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:52,600
But now our chance has finally come.

361
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:56,960
I already have a way
to get revenge on them.

362
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,600
What are you talking about?

363
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:07,320
This is the latest clip Singha posted.

364
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:13,000
<i>Hello, I'm Singha Darathong,</i>

365
00:26:13,080 --> 00:26:14,960
<i>the second-generation executive</i>
<i>of Darathong Music.</i>

366
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:16,880
<i>Our label is a country music label.</i>

367
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:21,280
Why are you showing me Singha's clip?

368
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:23,360
I'm not showing you Singha.

369
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,880
<i>…for the support we've had</i>
<i>for over 20 years.</i>

370
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:30,320
I'm showing you the teddy bear
with the green ribbon tied behind it.

371
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:31,440
The teddy bear?

372
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:33,400
Yes.

373
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:36,440
Their secret is hidden
inside that teddy bear.

374
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:46,480
Everything must be recorded in here.

375
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:55,280
What do I do?

376
00:26:56,360 --> 00:26:57,280
I need to hide it.

377
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:16,200
<i>Today, I have good news for everyone.</i>

378
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:18,680
<i>For those who love singing,</i>

379
00:27:18,760 --> 00:27:22,000
<i>you're invited to apply</i>
<i>for our singing competition.</i>

380
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:23,840
We have to get that teddy bear,

381
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,080
so we can rip off their mask.

382
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:29,120
<i>…and become the new singer</i>
<i>of Darathong Music.</i>

383
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:32,600
Then let me do it.
I'll steal the teddy bear.

384
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:42,920
- Poona.
- Poona.

385
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,680
What Aunt Wilai said makes sense.

386
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:56,960
If we don't fight back,

387
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:00,680
we'll have to live in shame
for the rest of our lives.

388
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:03,160
Why do we have to keep suffering

389
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,680
and living in hiding?

390
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,840
If we have a chance to fight back,

391
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:14,600
we have to take it. I'm willing to help.

392
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:16,480
It's too dangerous, Poona.

393
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:18,920
I don't want you putting yourself

394
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:22,400
at risk like that.
If anything happens to you,

395
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:24,880
I'll never forgive myself
for the rest of my life.

396
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:28,920
I can't stand seeing my father
being humiliated like this either, Uncle.

397
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:32,800
My father was once a famous singer.

398
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:35,200
Everyone knew his songs.

399
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:38,240
But after he died,

400
00:28:38,320 --> 00:28:40,320
his name was smeared with lies.

401
00:28:43,080 --> 00:28:45,360
I want to restore his honor.

402
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,400
Poona's right.

403
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,720
Our chance has come,
and we have to seize it.

404
00:28:58,240 --> 00:29:01,200
If we're doing this,
the first thing she has to do

405
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:04,760
is apply for the singing competition

406
00:29:04,840 --> 00:29:05,960
at Darathong Music.

407
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:09,560
Please, Uncle.

408
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:15,400
Let me enter the singing competition.

409
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:37,600
I think the situation here
is getting worse every day.

410
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:40,440
I think so too.

411
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:44,520
Oh my.

412
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:46,320
Huh?

413
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:50,600
Who's that sneaking around
in front of the house?

414
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,720
Could he be a thief?

415
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,720
He's secretly taking pictures of Chaiya.

416
00:30:03,320 --> 00:30:05,280
He must be some kind of pervert!

417
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,160
Help! A perverted thief!

418
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:09,960
A perverted thief! Help!

419
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,240
Where did he go?

420
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:16,160
Don't you run! I'm going to catch you.
Just wait and see!

421
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:18,240
Chaiya! Manat!

422
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:19,560
Oh dear.

423
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,920
- I'm going to faint!
- Oh.

424
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:22,080
Here's the thing.

425
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:23,680
Hold on. Did you see that?

426
00:30:23,760 --> 00:30:25,160
Did you see that man just now?

427
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:27,680
He was secretly
taking pictures of you, Chaiya.

428
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:30,120
I have a really bad feeling about this.

429
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:32,360
Hey, the dog! The dog's got the trash!

430
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,560
Excuse me for a second.

431
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,320
Shoo! Shoo!

432
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,040
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

433
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:44,640
Split up and look for him.

434
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:49,520
Hey, stop!

435
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:55,440
Why were you taking pictures of me?

436
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:58,200
I know you two are police informants.

437
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,520
I'm honored to have my picture
in your camera.

438
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,080
Chaiya!

439
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:13,200
Get out here!

440
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,280
I said get out here!

441
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:20,040
Whoa, bro. You're out of ammo.

442
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:21,600
How?

443
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:32,000
Hey!

444
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:12,000
Move.

445
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:23,160
He knows we're cops.

446
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:24,400
Huh?

447
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:26,320
Damn it.

448
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:27,880
Go after him.

449
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:38,160
Pick up!

450
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:40,760
What is it, Man?

451
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:41,760
Hello, Chit.

452
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,520
Hello? What are you saying?
I can't understand a word.

453
00:32:45,600 --> 00:32:47,200
Why is there no signal?

454
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:48,120
<i>Hello?</i>

455
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,320
Man?

456
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:52,520
Man!

457
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:54,960
Listen, I got photos
of the police informants.

458
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,440
<i>The photos are on my phone.</i>

459
00:32:56,520 --> 00:32:58,440
They were disguised as…

460
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:00,400
Meet me at the music label.

461
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:01,400
<i>I'll head there now.</i>

462
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:03,680
Okay. Got it.

463
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:30,240
What should we do?

464
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,680
DARATHONG

465
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,880
Mr. Singha!

466
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:47,960
Mr. Singha, get inside!

467
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:06,720
Hey! Man.

468
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:09,440
Man!

469
00:34:18,080 --> 00:34:19,440
Where is his phone?

470
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:23,239
Who took my guy's phone?

471
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:26,000
I don't know. I didn't see anything.

472
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:28,520
I'm asking who took it!

473
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:31,320
And who touched my man's body?

474
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:33,880
Oh, those two.

475
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:35,520
They went up close to look at the body.

476
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:37,679
Hey!

477
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:39,440
Who are you two?

478
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:42,040
Turn around!

479
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:44,719
Turn around right now! Bring them here!

480
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:55,080
Search them.

481
00:34:58,080 --> 00:35:01,120
Hey, take it easy, man.
You got a warrant or what?

482
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:05,600
No warrant. Just bullets. Want some?

483
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:08,680
That's mine.

484
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,240
That's mine too.

485
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:24,400
Did you search him properly?
Check everywhere.

486
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:26,440
I searched everywhere.

487
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:30,160
Only my underwear's left.
Wanna search that too?

488
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:38,800
Hey.

489
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:46,440
What's going on here?

490
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,720
Man got photos of the police informants.

491
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,320
I told him to bring it here
so I could see it.

492
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:57,160
But I think these two stole the phone.

493
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:04,760
Where did you hide the phone?

494
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:08,720
Is this the one?

495
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:16,600
Yes, that's Man's phone.

496
00:36:17,600 --> 00:36:19,400
Hey, did you steal this, Sarge?

497
00:36:19,480 --> 00:36:21,520
Hey, watch it. I ought to charge you

498
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:24,680
for insulting an officer.
I saw it fly off over there.

499
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:26,520
Hand it over.

500
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:34,440
Why do you seem so anxious?

501
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:37,160
Is there something important
on that phone?

502
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:42,520
No.

503
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:45,160
It's probably broken anyway.

504
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:49,760
Hey, how did you two end up here?

505
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:54,320
We were out filming content for YouTube,

506
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:56,200
and then we saw people
shooting over there.

507
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:59,560
This guy accused me
of stealing a dead man's phone,

508
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,240
when I was only trying to help.

509
00:37:03,080 --> 00:37:05,080
I need both of you
to stay and give a statement.

510
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:08,160
You too, Mr. Singha.

511
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,880
Fine, but make it quick.
I'm not free all day.

512
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:15,480
Once the questioning is done,
hurry up and find

513
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:17,320
whoever tried to shoot me.

514
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,760
Of course. Whoever committed the crime

515
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:21,600
will not escape the law.

516
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,680
We'll wait over there for now.

517
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:28,280
Seeing blood makes me feel faint.

518
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:32,600
Same here.

519
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:35,040
I'm feeling weak,
like I'm coming down with a fever.

520
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:36,560
We're out.

521
00:37:37,280 --> 00:37:38,640
Don't forget to give your statement.

522
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:40,560
Okay.

523
00:37:49,880 --> 00:37:50,960
How did it go, Captain?

524
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,440
It went well, Sergeant.

525
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:54,880
If it weren't for you,
I'd have been in serious trouble.

526
00:37:59,520 --> 00:38:01,200
Excuse me.

527
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:03,120
Sorry, Auntie!

528
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:04,160
Whoa, bro!

529
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:10,120
Someone call an ambulance, please.

530
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:18,080
Looks like none of his family
is here either.

531
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:19,880
Such a shame.
He had his whole life ahead of him.

532
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:26,680
Sergeant Yot,
this is the dead man's phone.

533
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,920
He managed to take photos
of Captain Chaiya and Lieutenant Manat.

534
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:31,120
Huh? That's bad.

535
00:38:31,200 --> 00:38:33,480
- I've already taken care of it.
- Okay.

536
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:35,080
I'll leave the rest to you.

537
00:38:35,160 --> 00:38:36,240
Got it.

538
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:40,360
We're all on the same team anyway.

539
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:44,280
Good deeds deserve good things.
Tonight, barbecue party.

540
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:45,880
Hey, really?

541
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:48,680
Oh, Captain.

542
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:49,840
Yes?

543
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:53,240
I got the plate number of the car
that targeted Singha.

544
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:55,680
Excellent, Sergeant.

545
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:58,960
Send it to me first,
but don't send it to Captain Tom just yet.

546
00:39:00,120 --> 00:39:01,640
Huh? Why not?

547
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,840
I want to check something first.

548
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:08,440
Alright. Sure.

549
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:19,920
DARATHONG

550
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,120
Dad!

551
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:24,600
Dad, are you alright?

552
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:26,160
I'm fine.

553
00:39:26,240 --> 00:39:29,160
Man took the bullet for me.

554
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:33,440
Officer, are you questioning him
right now?

555
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:34,560
Yes.

556
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:36,880
Then may I stay and sit in on this?

557
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:38,080
- Of course.
- Thank you.

558
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:42,280
Mr. Singha, do you have any idea

559
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,960
why someone tried to shoot you this time?

560
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:47,440
Well, it's probably something
related to business.

561
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:49,360
Which business exactly?

562
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:52,320
As far as I know, you're involved
in quite a few businesses.

563
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:55,360
If you suspect anyone in particular,
you should tell the officer.

564
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:56,320
Hey.

565
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,680
How can I accuse someone
without any basis?

566
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:01,120
Yes, Dad.

567
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,360
Please give me information
on any business rivals

568
00:40:03,440 --> 00:40:05,600
you think may be behind this incident.

569
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:08,200
Save this for another day.

570
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:13,240
Do you have any sense at all?

571
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:17,400
Mr. Singha has just been through
something traumatic.

572
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:20,160
And you're pressing him
for answers right now?

573
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,760
- But…
- No buts.

574
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:24,720
Go investigate and find the culprit.

575
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:27,960
Question the villagers
who witnessed the incident first.

576
00:40:28,560 --> 00:40:29,440
Yes, sir.

577
00:40:36,440 --> 00:40:38,800
That subordinate of yours
seems very determined.

578
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:43,480
One day it may backfire on him.

579
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:50,560
How are you, Mr. Singha? Are you hurt?

580
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:53,920
No, I'm fine.

581
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:56,960
Would you like me to assign
police officers to protect you,

582
00:40:57,760 --> 00:40:59,160
in case they come back?

583
00:40:59,240 --> 00:41:02,320
Or we can arrange a police escort
when you travel,

584
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:04,480
so no one can try to attack you again.

585
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:06,360
That won't be necessary.

586
00:41:07,320 --> 00:41:08,760
My men can handle it.

587
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:12,640
But thank you very much, Superintendent,

588
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:14,680
for your concern.

589
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:18,280
Alright then, if you need anything,

590
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:20,080
let me know immediately.

591
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:22,440
I'll arrange everything.

592
00:41:22,960 --> 00:41:24,400
Certainly.

593
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:26,720
Then I'll head back to the station first.

594
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:29,280
Thank you.

595
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:30,880
Let's go.

596
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:41,960
So who tried to shoot Singha?

597
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:44,440
Take the license plate Sergeant Au got

598
00:41:44,520 --> 00:41:47,680
and run a check first.
Find out who the car belongs to.

599
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:50,320
Right, of course. I'll handle it.

600
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:53,680
Hey, could that be the one?

601
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:58,200
Yeah.

602
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:00,240
Let's take a closer look.

603
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:01,920
Come on.

604
00:42:15,560 --> 00:42:17,160
What are you two doing near my car?

605
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:18,240
Nothing.

606
00:42:18,320 --> 00:42:20,600
I'm livestreaming.
Just looking for a good spot.

607
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:22,640
Is this your car?

608
00:42:22,720 --> 00:42:25,800
Yeah. The renter never brought it back.

609
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:28,440
He left it here. I tracked it down by GPS.

610
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:31,680
Wait, this is a rental car?

611
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:34,520
Yeah. The renter used
fake documents to rent it

612
00:42:34,600 --> 00:42:35,960
and didn't return it on time.

613
00:42:36,040 --> 00:42:37,560
They might've been using it
to transport drugs.

614
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:41,600
Alright.

615
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:43,520
We'll get going then.

616
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:55,960
<i>I've waited</i>

617
00:42:56,600 --> 00:43:02,320
<i>Waited so long</i>
<i>My heart unwavering and full</i>

618
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:05,760
<i>But he's forgotten</i>

619
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:12,440
<i>Forgotten me, with no certainty at all</i>

620
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:17,600
<i>I wait for him, but he forgets I'm waiting</i>

621
00:43:17,680 --> 00:43:20,160
<i>Waiting and pleading</i>

622
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:23,960
<i>With this lonely heart</i>

623
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:30,560
<i>Still waiting</i>

624
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:31,800
Use your diaphragm.

625
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:37,680
<i>I kept hoping until I grew weary</i>

626
00:43:37,760 --> 00:43:41,880
<i>Still waiting</i>

627
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:47,880
<i>For that heartless one</i>
<i>Crying day and night</i>

628
00:43:47,960 --> 00:43:50,200
<i>He forgot his promise</i>

629
00:43:50,280 --> 00:43:55,480
<i>Leaving this sad country girl behind</i>
<i>Waiting for him</i>

630
00:43:55,560 --> 00:44:00,000
<i>Waiting for him alone</i>

631
00:44:01,960 --> 00:44:05,360
‪DARATHONG

632
00:44:08,720 --> 00:44:10,720
- Oh.
- Hello, boss.

633
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:12,760
- Hello.
- Hello.

634
00:44:12,840 --> 00:44:14,280
Do you remember me?

635
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:17,760
I'm the once-famous singer,

636
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:19,720
Boonprueng Fueangnakhara.

637
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,040
Of course I remember.

638
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:23,800
Back then, we competed
in singing contests together all the time.

639
00:44:23,880 --> 00:44:26,960
If I hadn't had an upset stomach that day,

640
00:44:27,040 --> 00:44:28,800
I would've beaten you in that contest.

641
00:44:30,440 --> 00:44:31,880
Here you go.

642
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:33,080
This is for you, boss.

643
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:35,280
I brought it as a gift.

644
00:44:35,360 --> 00:44:36,720
Oh, come on, what boss?

645
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:39,560
Just call me Singha. We're old friends.

646
00:44:39,640 --> 00:44:41,040
Thank you very much.

647
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,280
- Joey.
- Yes, sir.

648
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:45,560
Take a photo for me.
I'm going to post it on social media.

649
00:44:47,600 --> 00:44:51,160
Mr. Sornrak, come stand with us.

650
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:55,240
Come here.

651
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:57,560
She got it from her dad.

652
00:44:58,080 --> 00:44:59,920
One, two, three.

653
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:01,360
Hit like, please.

654
00:45:02,640 --> 00:45:03,920
A mini heart too.

655
00:45:05,120 --> 00:45:06,440
All done, sir.

656
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:08,520
Thank you very much.

657
00:45:08,600 --> 00:45:09,440
Not at all.

658
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:11,320
- Have a seat, Village Head.
- Alright.

659
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:20,440
Is this your daughter?

660
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:22,120
Hello.

661
00:45:22,200 --> 00:45:23,200
Hello.

662
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:24,800
Yes, my daughter. Her name is Maria.

663
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:28,640
If Mr. Sornrak hadn't helped her
the other day,

664
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:30,640
she would've been in real trouble.

665
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:34,320
That's why I came by today
to thank you, boss.

666
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:36,840
It's nothing. No need to thank me.

667
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:38,840
It was simply my duty as a good citizen.

668
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:42,200
There's one more thing.

669
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:45,560
I saw that Darathong Music
is holding a singing competition,

670
00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:48,440
so I'd like to apply as well.

671
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:50,640
Alright, Village Head.

672
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:53,000
- Since we're old friends,
- Yes.

673
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:56,240
Maria doesn't need to go audition

674
00:45:56,320 --> 00:45:58,560
or do a voice test in the other room.

675
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:00,840
Let her sing right here
for me and Sornrak.

676
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:02,760
We'll listen right here. How about that?

677
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:05,280
Thank you, boss.

678
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:12,000
<i>I've waited</i>

679
00:46:12,080 --> 00:46:17,840
<i>Waited so long</i>
<i>My heart unwavering and full</i>

680
00:46:17,920 --> 00:46:22,240
<i>But he's forgotten</i>

681
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:28,240
<i>Forgotten me, with no certainty at all</i>

682
00:46:28,320 --> 00:46:31,280
<i>I wait for him</i>

683
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:33,760
<i>But he forgets I'm waiting</i>

684
00:46:33,840 --> 00:46:36,720
<i>Waiting and pleading</i>

685
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:42,120
<i>With this lonely heart</i>

686
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,600
Three, four.

687
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:49,520
<i>If you don't love me</i>
<i>Why didn't you say so?</i>

688
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:51,080
<i>Cha, cha, cha</i>

689
00:46:51,160 --> 00:46:52,840
<i>Why come and fool me</i>
<i>Just to toy with my heart?</i>

690
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:54,520
<i>Cha, cha, cha</i>

691
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:57,600
<i>Oh, you fickle-hearted man</i>

692
00:46:57,680 --> 00:47:00,880
<i>I can't take this anymore</i>

693
00:47:00,960 --> 00:47:02,360
<i>Have you forgotten how we first met?</i>

694
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:04,240
<i>Cha, cha, cha</i>

695
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:06,080
<i>A woman loves</i>
<i>But you pretend not to care</i>

696
00:47:06,160 --> 00:47:07,800
<i>Cha, cha, cha</i>

697
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,360
<i>So cold and distant</i>

698
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:13,560
<i>Men like you deserve a slap</i>

699
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:17,800
Teacher.

700
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:21,280
Poona, how was it?
What did they do inside?

701
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:24,120
They had me sing live
and then did an interview.

702
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,360
Do you think you'll get in?

703
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:28,560
I'm not really sure, Teacher.

704
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:30,880
I think you will.

705
00:47:30,960 --> 00:47:32,280
You've got to make it.

706
00:47:32,360 --> 00:47:33,960
Do I need to pray for good luck too?

707
00:47:34,920 --> 00:47:36,560
I can do it!

708
00:47:36,640 --> 00:47:38,560
<i>Before I ever loved you</i>

709
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:40,000
<i>You used to sweet talk me</i>

710
00:47:40,080 --> 00:47:42,960
<i>Your words were always so sweet</i>
<i>And never ending</i>

711
00:47:43,040 --> 00:47:46,040
<i>But once I fell in love with you</i>
<i>Loved you blindly</i>

712
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:49,600
<i>You went and broke my heart</i>

713
00:47:49,680 --> 00:47:52,560
<i>If you didn't love me</i>
<i>Why didn't you say so?</i>

714
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:56,080
<i>Why did you come and fool me</i>
<i>Leaving me confused?</i>

715
00:47:56,160 --> 00:47:57,320
<i>From now on, I…</i>

716
00:47:57,400 --> 00:48:00,200
Teacher, isn't that Maria's voice?

717
00:48:14,240 --> 00:48:16,560
Hey! Let's go to the police station.

718
00:48:16,640 --> 00:48:18,080
NEXT EPISODE

719
00:48:18,160 --> 00:48:20,280
He claims to hate drugs,

720
00:48:20,360 --> 00:48:23,720
yet he keeps drug dealers as his men?

721
00:48:24,800 --> 00:48:26,440
Believe it if you want,

722
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:28,520
but I don't buy it.

723
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:31,120
Open it!

724
00:48:33,120 --> 00:48:35,280
Oh my God, blood! Blood!

725
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:37,560
Did you really have to do this to me?

726
00:48:38,240 --> 00:48:40,800
This is bullying. I'll remove your name.

727
00:51:02,920 --> 00:51:05,080
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
